48QYBxkNz3bQ7QEzPOWxVrvNKyv2.contactDetails: Studying at UBB is not just an academic journey; it's a life-changing experience! Connect and share insights with peers from around the world in an academic environment steeped in tradition and excellence. Venture together beyond the classroom and discover Romania's captivating Carpathian landscapes and the mysteries of Transylvanian tales. With Cluj-Napoca as your vibrant backdrop, immerse yourself in a city where festivals celebrate our diverse heritage, and café conversations unveil new perspectives. At UBB, is not just about academics; it's about broadening horizons and evolving into a more enlightened version of yourself, all within the warm embrace of the EU.
48QYBxkNz3bQ7QEzPOWxVrvNKyv2.updated_at: Thu Sep 14 2023 09:27:46 GMT+0300 (Eastern European Summer Time)

6mh0O7oSDpdie71QX2av6BQoLw02.contactDetails: Sorbonne University Abu Dhabi is a French and English-speaking university established on 7 October 2006 in Abu Dhabi, the capital city of the United Arab Emirates. The university is affiliated with the French Sorbonne University in the United Arab Emirates.

BEjTcqvuG9QAqdr59Pbw7D0qSVT2.contactDetails: Koç University, founded in 1993 in Istanbul, Turkey, is a distinguished non-profit, research-intensive, private institution known for its dedication to excellence in education. Following an American-style curriculum, the university offers a world-class learning experience entirely conducted in English. With seven colleges featuring 22 undergraduate programs (in Administrative Sciences, Engineering, Sciences, Social Sciences, Medicine, and Nursing) and four graduate schools offering 40 master's and 28 PhD programs, Koç University welcomes over 8600 students from Turkey and around the globe from +83 countries.

Ps9i24nH4aPU9rR0I7fB99SS1vl2.contactDetails: The American University of Ras Al Khaimah (AURAK) is a public, non-profit, independent, coeducation institution of higher education. Zf1Q2Lwt5La9MoFwiG97yWUbkdi1.contactDetails:
Welcome to Staffordshire University. We’re proud to be an award-winning institution that places students at the heart of everything we do. Staffordshire University is rated among the UK's top 10 universities for Teaching Quality and Social Inclusion (The Times and The Sunday Times Good University Guide 2023), and is a well-regarded research institution, with 87 per cent of its research rated as world leading or of international importance (Research Excellence Framework 2021). The University is connected in other ways too. Digitally innovative, with strong industry links and a mission to provide the next generation of education opportunities. 

The schools and faculties of Staffordshire University are made up of academic experts that work closely with industry leaders to ensure that students are learning things that will benefit them when they move into the world of work. With campuses in Stoke-on-Trent, London and Stafford, Staffordshire University provides students with the perfect base from which to explore the rest of the country. With much of the UK within a couple of hours' travel away, students have easy access to some of the most famous cities in Europe.

WHO WE ARE
Home to a global network of more than 20,000 students, Staffordshire University has always been ahead of the game.
From championing digital innovation to preparing students for careers in emerging industries, we provide next generation education opportunities. It’s a key reason why we are ranked 2nd in the UK for quality education (Sustainable Development Goal 4, THE Impact Rankings 2023).
Our main Stoke-on-Trent campus is in the centre of England. We also have a Stafford campus specialising in healthcare education and a London campus dedicated to tech-related courses.
But our reach is worldwide, with more than 8,700 full-time students based at partner institutions in the UK and internationally.
Staffordshire University offers a wide variety of undergraduate and postgraduate courses, including degrees in computing, business, engineering, law, and art and design.
We have a growing international reputation for academic research as well. In the 2021 Research Excellence Framework, 68% of our research was rated as “world-leading” or “internationally excellent”. And 87% of our research impact was classed as “very considerable” or “outstanding”.

OUR HISTORY
Staffordshire University was founded in 1914 as an institution specialising in science and technology and later became a polytechnic. We were officially given university status in 1992.
It all began for us in Stoke-on-Trent, a city in the heart of the UK that’s renowned as the world capital of ceramics. We are proud of our heritage and extensive links with industry.
Our main campus is still based in Stoke-on-Trent, which was a finalist for the 2021 UK City of Culture. But over the years, we have grown substantially and now have several other campuses too.

OUR FUTURE
We aim to be the UK’s most digitally innovative university, leading the way with hyper-personalised learning that will prepare students for jobs of the future.
Digital has been part of Staffordshire University’s DNA for more than half a century. We were the first UK university to launch a computing degree in the 1960s and have never looked back. More recently, we became the first to move to the cloud and to introduce an AI-powered digital assistant for our students.
Our curriculum ensures students get real-world experiences and can put their skills into practice using simulation-based facilities.
Our healthcare students, for instance, have access to simulated hospital wards and operating theatres, along with the world’s largest immersive training suite. Using virtual reality, life-like backdrops can be projected onto the walls to place them at the heart of the action.
Other facilities include a mock courtroom for law students and a crime scene house where forensic students can perfect their investigative skills.

OUR ACCOLADES:
We are ranked:
•	2nd in the UK for quality education (Sustainable Development Goal 4, THE Impact Rankings 2023)
•	Top 10 for career prospects (Whatuni Student Choice Awards 2023)
•	Top 20 for facilities (Whatuni Student Choice Awards 2023)
•	Top 10 for social inclusion (The Times and The Sunday Times Good University Guide 2023)
•	4* (Qs Star Ratings 2021).

Established in 1967, Georgian College (Canada) is a public college with 130+ market-driven programs offered to over 13,000 full time students including about 4,500 international students from 85 countries.
Its 100-acre flagship campus, located in Barrie, is just an hour north of Toronto. Georgian College also has 6 other campuses located within the Georgian Bay area. A leader in work experience-integrated programs, Georgian students get the opportunity to work with 6,200 employers across Canada within the college network. A leader in work experience-integrated programs, Georgian College has one of the highest graduate employment rates among Ontario colleges. 88.1% of Georgian alumni found work within six months of graduation – well above the provincial average, which they’ve exceeded for 20 years.
Georgian is the first and only college in Canada designated a changemaker college by Ashoka U for their role as a leader in social innovation and changemaking in higher education.

Georgian College also offers an excellent English Language program with 7 week modules going from Level 1 to 8 within its main campus. 
The college is renowned for its programs in Aviation, Automotive, Business, Community Services, Design & Visual Arts, Health & Wellness, Hospitality, Information Technology and Electrical, Marine, Mechanical, Power & Sustainable Technology. The college boasts of state-of-the-art equipment and facilities for all its programs. The hallmark of all its programs is the opportunity for every student to get ample hands-on training and individual practice time. 
Georgian College offers 1-year certificates, 2-year diplomas and 3-year advanced diplomas, 1-year post-graduate certificates (additionally 1 exceptional 2-year post-graduate certificate program), many  bachelor degrees and combined degree-diploma programs with Lakehead University. Georgian programs boast an impressive 800 transfer agreements with 59 institutions across the globe.
Co-op programs give students the opportunity to make money during their co-op semesters (estimate of $6,000 to $8,000 per semester).
